"VIM REGULAR EXPRESSIONS
""""""""""""""""""""""""
" /\v :for very macgic regexmode
""""""""""""""""""""""""
"body   {color:#3c3c3c;}
"a   {color:#0000EE;}
"strong   {color:#000;}
"/\v#([0-9a-fA-F]{6}|[0-9a-fA-F]{3})
"shorter version: /\v#(\x{6}|\x{3})
"use \x :to substitude [0-9a-fA-F]
"/\v#(\x{6}|\x{3})  :to match 6 or 3 hex digits in a row ,eg: #000 #fff #333 #ff00ff
"""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
"USE V TO ACTIVATE VERY MAGIC SEARCH
""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
"The N key searches backward...
"...thev pattern switch(a.k.a.very magic search)...
"use /aka will be match too much unwanted characters
""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
"USE V TO ACTIVATE VERY NOMAGIC SEARCH
"/\Va.k.a
""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
"THIS REGEX IS USE TO CLEAN THE REPEAT WORDS
"/\v<(\w+)\_s+\1+> : to match the word and the _s+ and the word again
""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
"gUgn : to make the first match upper case
"/\vX(ht)?ml\C<CR> : to match html or xhtml
""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
"Xï¼šåŒ¹é… XhtmlDocument å’Œ XhtmlTag ä¸­çš„ Xã€‚
"(ht)?ï¼šåŒ¹é… Xhtml ä¸­çš„ htï¼Œæˆ–è€…å¯ä»¥å¿½ç•¥ htï¼Œç›´æ¥åŒ¹é… Xmlï¼ˆå¦‚æœåªæ˜¯ htmlï¼‰ã€‚
"mlï¼šåŒ¹é… mlã€‚
"\Cï¼šå¿½ç•¥å¤§å°å†™ï¼Œæ‰€ä»¥æ— è®ºæ˜¯ Xhtml è¿˜æ˜¯ XHTML éƒ½èƒ½åŒ¹é…ã€‚
""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
"class XhtmlDocument < XmlDocument;end
"class XhtmlTag < XmlTag;end
"""""""""
"example:
"""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
"This string contains a'quoted' word.
"This string contains 'two' quoted 'words'.
"This 'string doesn't make things easy'.
"""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
"regex1: /\v'.+' : match the quoted word will show three matches which is : 'quoted', 'two' quoted 'words', 'string doesn't make things easy'
"regex2: /\v'[^']+': match the quoted word will show two matches which is : 'quoted', 'two' quoted 'words',and  'string doesn'
"regex3:/\v'([^']|'\w)+': match the quoted word will show two matches which is : 'quoted', 'two'  'words',and  'string doesn't make things easy'
